body:
@alcortazzo Can you share your `alacritty -vv` output log?

~~Generally you should be able to set the initial/minimum window size in your window manager assuming you're on X11.~~

Just saw that you're both on KDE+Wayland, have you experienced this in any other applications? This sounds like it might be an issue with KDE Wayland specifically. You said you encountered this after a system upgrade, can you downgrade to your last previous KDE version and see if that fixes things?

> [2021-11-13 12:37:18.541347012] [INFO ] [alacritty] glutin event: WindowEvent { window_id: WindowId(Wayland(WindowId(94331396022688))), event: Resized(PhysicalSize { width: 2, height: 1 }) }

Yeah, there's clearly a resize event coming in telling us to go to 2x1. That's strange.

Can you share the `WAYLAND_DEBUG=1 alacritty 2>&1 | grep "configure"` output?
